# Documentation Maker

This project uses **Documentation Maker** to keep auto-generated, commit-tracked docs up to date.

## Where docs live

```
code-docs/
├── structure/
│   ├── file-structure.md   ← project folder layout and purposes
│   └── dependencies.md     ← import/dependency graph
└── files/                  ← one .md per source file
    └── <path__with__underscores>.md
```

## How to help as an AI agent

- **Explaining a file** → read `code-docs/files/<path>.md` first; it has context and change history.
- **After editing a file** → suggest updating its doc in `code-docs/files/` if the change is significant.
- **New file with no doc** → generate one using the format from existing docs in `code-docs/files/`.
- **Project structure questions** → read `code-docs/structure/file-structure.md`.

## Per-file doc format

Every file doc ends with a change history table — **append rows, never delete them**:

```markdown
## Change History

| Commit   | Date       | What Changed                          |
|----------|------------|---------------------------------------|
| abc1234  | 2026-06-05 | Added OAuth flow, removed legacy token |
```

## Keyboard shortcuts

| Action        | Windows / Linux     | Mac                 |
|---------------|---------------------|---------------------|
| Initial setup | Ctrl+Alt+D I        | Cmd+Alt+D I         |
| Update docs   | Ctrl+Alt+D U        | Cmd+Alt+D U         |
